Pliny complains that the centumviral court, in which his practice lies, is being rapidly deteriorated by the audacity oi the younger pleaders, and the paid applause of their audience.

Vemm opinaris: distringor centumviralibus causis, quae me exercent magis quam delectant. Sunt enim pleraeque parvae et exiles: raro incidit vel personarum claritate vel negotii magnitudine insignis.
